parameter.name: Key-follow 1
parameter.help: Relationship between note pitch and volume of the sound. A value of 2 specifies an equal volume for all pitches, and is the default

parameter.name: Key-follow 2
parameter.help: Relationship between note pitch and volume of the sound. A value of 2 specifies an equal volume for all pitches, and is the default

parameter.name: Stretch tuning
parameter.help: Specifies the stretch tuning, a.k.a. Railsback curve. 0 should be used for most instruments, while 1-7 may be suitable for piano or electric piano sounds

parameter.name: DSP chain name
parameter.help: Name of the DSP chain. This is not used for anything and can be set to any string

parameter.name: DSP chain number
parameter.help: Number of the DSP chain. This is not used for anything and can be set to any value

parameter.name: Volume 3
parameter.help: Volume of the note.\nOnly notes played on the keyboard are affected by this (not MIDI IN or rhythms)
